          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1R"/>
                              <p rend="align(center)">
                                        <placeName>Richmond</placeName>
                                        <date><sic>oct</sic> 14<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1829</date>
                              </p>
                              <p>My Dear <addressee>Isaac</addressee></p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">after a very <sic>pleasand</sic> passage I arrived
                                        here last night 7 o clock<lb/> found Aunt and all our
                                        friends in good health, all are pleased with the<lb/>
                                        <sic>acount</sic> I gave them about
                                                  <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> particularly
                                        of the kind treat=<lb/>ment I Received of our friend
                                                  <persName>Mr Mrs Piexatto</persName> your servt
                                        and myself<lb/> wish very much to have it in any power to
                                        return the same at any<lb/> time if ever they should come
                                        our way so far for myself, but the<lb/> attention paid to
                                        you has made an ever lasting impression in my<lb/> mind that
                                        never shall be <sic>forgoten</sic>, I am sure you will do
                                        all in your<lb/> power to serve them with all your might, my
                                        dear <persName>Isaac</persName> I hope you will Try<lb/> To
                                        cultivate the friendship of <sic>every body</sic> in your
                                        Congregation and not mind<lb/> some few <sic>thinks</sic>
                                        which now and then you might <sic>recieve</sic>, never
                                        interfere with<lb/> my <sic>differance</sic> between them,
                                        but be a peace maker and make them friends<lb/> Remember one
                                        kindly to my friends <persName>Mr and Mrs. [?]
                                                  Philips</persName> to <persName>Mrs
                                                  Cohin</persName> and<lb/> her worthy sons
                                        Daughters to old <persName>Mrs Philips</persName> my old
                                                  <sic>acquaintence</sic>
                                        <persName>Mrs Hart</persName> Mr [?]<lb/> from[?]
                                                  <persName>Mrs Piso</persName> to the Dear girls at
                                        our friend <persName>Mr Piexatto</persName> and all the rest
                                        of my<lb/> friends in
                                                  <placeName><sic>philadelphia</sic></placeName>
                                        your aunt <persName>Mrs Depass Rina[?] Abby</persName> send
                                                  <sic>there</sic><lb/> love to you and I Remain
                                        your <sic>affectional</sic> uncle and friend</p>
                              <p rend="indent(11)">
                                        <persName role="author">Zalma Rehine</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p>NB so you turned informer, what tell your Aunt about the girls to
                                        be<lb/> sure that was well done I'll make her be afraid to
                                        let me go from home<lb/> without her, take care I shall [?]
                                        when ever in my power</p>
                              <p rend="indent(10)">[?] god bless you</p>
                              <p>tell <persName>Mrs Piexotto</persName> that I carred[?] the cake
                                        all the to <placeName>Richmond</placeName> to treat<lb/>
                                        <persName role="author">Mrs Rehine</persName> with her
                                        present Aunt was mighty pleased with it<lb/> let us hear
                                        from you soon.</p>
                              <pb n="2V"/>
                              <p>
                                        <persName>Mr Isaac Leeser</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p>to the care of <persName>Mr A. C. Piexotto</persName></p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                              </p>
